    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Harold E. Stassen</persName>, Director of
                    the Mutual Security Administration, visited Western Europe between January 31
                    and February 8, 1953 for a series of conferences and discussions with various
                    American and European officials on outstanding problems facing the Western
                    alliance including the <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>. For documentation on
                    the <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>–<persName
                        corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Stassen</persName> trip to Europe in January and
                    February 1953, see <ref target="frus1952-54v05p2#pg_1548">pages 1548</ref>
                    ff.</p>
            </div>
